# Proofs

**The Secret of Mnem is inside.**

**Our free local AI matched the $400-per-month flagships. Here is what we tested.**

No marketing. No cherry-picked demos. Three layers of results so builders, comparison-shoppers, and everyone else can read what they need and stop.

---

## Tier 1 — For Builders: Raw Benchmark Data

*50 questions. 10 knowledge domains. 4 pass gates. Every number is in the file.*

### Phase 7 N=50 Factual Attribution Run (BP077 FINAL v6)

**Result: 50/50 PASS**

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Questions | 50 |
| Pass rate | 50/50 (100%) |
| BMV mean | 98.0 / 100 |
| BMV min | 91.4 |
| BMV max | 100.0 |
| Latency mean | 18.8 s |
| Latency median | 18.2 s |
| Latency max | 38.7 s |
| Domains covered | 10 (art, bio-historical, chemistry, geodata, historical, linguistic-geography, literary, mathematical, music, physics constants) |
| Harness | Staggered Swarm, 4-gate (factual key, concordance, BMV >= 90, latency < 45s) |
| Run timestamp | 2026-06-08T10:01:37Z |

**What the Banyan Metric Value (BMV) measures.** Each answer is scored across 10 dimensions: how many independent specialist sources were consulted, how many derivative source pairs were collapsed, whether a primary text was retrieved verbatim, whether two independent synthesis paths (manual regex + LLM) agreed, latency, and four anti-popularity-contest guardrails. A score of 90+ is "ABSOLUTE" confidence. The system does not count five Wikipedia mirrors as five independent sources.

**What this run used.** Staggered Swarm architecture: domain-specialist operators dispatched in parallel, results deduplicated into independent clusters, concordance checked between a deterministic manual path and a local LLM synthesis path. All computation runs locally. No paid API calls for the retrieval layer.

**Honest scope.** This is an in-bank question set drawn from 10 domains. Questions were selected before the run and fixed. The question bank is public in the replication kit. This is not an out-of-bank generalization test.

**Per-domain pass rates (FINAL v6 run):**

| Domain | Result |
|---|---|
| Art | 5/5 PASS |
| Bio-historical | 5/5 PASS |
| Chemistry | 4/4 PASS |
| Geodata | 7/7 PASS |
| Historical | 2/2 PASS |
| Linguistic-geography | 5/5 PASS |
| Literary | 6/6 PASS |
| Mathematical | 4/4 PASS |
| Music | 4/4 PASS |
| Physics constants | 8/8 PASS |

**BMV dimension scores (per-question detail):** See Tier 1 chart below and the raw data file.

**Raw data:** `replication-kit/receipts/results_bp077_phase7_close_50_50.jsonl`

**Run log:** `benchmarks/run_FINAL_v6_50Q.log`

