## Tier 2 — For Comparison-Shoppers: RoseBush vs Paid Flagships

*How does a free local AI stack up on the dimensions that matter for real use?*

The table below compares RoseBush (Free Gemma 4 12B + Mnem-DRT + mesh) running on a mid-range consumer laptop against four paid flagship services on five dimensions. Numbers for RoseBush come from Phase 7 N=50 (above). Numbers for flagships come from public published benchmarks and pricing pages; sources are cited on each row.

| Dimension | RoseBush (Phase 7) | Claude 4 Opus | GPT-4o | Gemini 2.5 Pro | Llama 3.1 405B |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Factual attribution (in-bank) | 50/50 BMV 98.0 | UNVERIFIED (see note) | UNVERIFIED (see note) | UNVERIFIED (see note) | UNVERIFIED (see note) |
| Cost per month (standard use) | $0 (local) | ~$200 to $400 (API) | ~$20 to $200 (API) | ~$20 to $200 (API) | Self-hosted: $0; API varies |
| Latency (first response) | 18.8 s mean (local, LAN) | ~1 to 3 s (network) | ~1 to 4 s (network) | ~1 to 3 s (network) | Varies by host |
| Privacy posture | Data stays on your machine | Data sent to Anthropic servers | Data sent to OpenAI servers | Data sent to Google servers | Self-hosted: local |
| Mesh shared knowledge | Yes -- cross-node, 20/20 hash-verified | No | No | No | No |

**Cost sources:** Anthropic pricing page (accessed 2026-06); OpenAI pricing page (accessed 2026-06); Google AI Studio / Vertex pricing page (accessed 2026-06). Pawn-fact-check recommended before publishing — API pricing changes frequently.

**Latency note.** MnemosyneC latency includes multi-source retrieval and swarm synthesis, not just LLM call time. Flagship API latency figures above reflect first-token-to-complete-response for typical queries. These are not the same measurement. Do not treat this as a direct speed race.

**UNVERIFIED rows.** We do not have a head-to-head run of Claude/GPT/Gemini on the same 50 questions using the same 4-gate BMV harness. The "UNVERIFIED" cells are honest blanks. Pawn-fact-check action: run flagships against `bp077_phase7_q50_bank.json` and report BMV-equivalent scores (see Tier 3 for the planned empirical head-to-head).

**What we can say from public data.** All four flagship models score in the 85-95 range on MMLU-Pro (public leaderboards, 2025-2026 vintage). MnemosyneC at 98.0 BMV on our in-bank factual-attribution set is not directly comparable to MMLU-Pro. Different questions, different harness. We are not claiming to beat flagships on MMLU-Pro. We are claiming that on member-specific factual-attribution tasks using local knowledge substrate, a free local setup can reach comparable confidence levels.

