## Trust Badges

### Wife Test: DONE

MnemosyneC was tested by a non-technical household member before release. The result was: the AI gave no response when the local model was not bundled. That test caught the single largest UX failure in v0.1.22. The fix shipped in v0.1.24: a bundled local model so the first answer works out of the box, zero setup required.

Real users break things that builders miss. We test with real users before we call anything done.

### Mesh Proof: 20/20 Hash-Verified (BP067, 2026-05-31)

Two physical machines on a home LAN. Machine 2 held data that Machine 1 did not have. Machine 1 queried Machine 2 via the mesh protocol. All 20 queries resolved correctly. All 20 answers hash-verified against the source data.

- M1: 192.168.86.30 (primary test node)
- M2: 192.168.86.45 (wife's machine, v0.1.21)
- p50 latency: 16.6 ms
- p95 latency: 25.8 ms
- Cross-node accuracy: 0/20 baseline (M1 alone, no M2 data) to 20/20 meshed

**What this proves.** More members means more knowledge available to each member. The network effect is real and it is measured.

**Honest cost disclosure.** Mesh transport = $0 (LAN TCP). The automated grading used in the test cost approximately $0.01 (Haiku-4.5 API calls for 20 questions). The mesh itself costs nothing to operate.

---

## Caveat Block (Truth-Always)

**What these results are:**
- Phase 7: in-bank factual-attribution test on a fixed 50-question set across 10 general knowledge domains. The same questions were used to tune the system. This measures ceiling performance on known question types, not generalization to unseen questions.
- BMV 98.0 is the mean on the FINAL v6 run (50/50 PASS). An earlier run (phase7_close.log) scored 45/50 with mean 95.5 and a different BMV floor. The FINAL v6 run incorporated architecture improvements. Both runs are in the repository.
- Mesh test: 20 questions, same-LAN, one data-push scenario. Data was pushed to M2 by a script, not organically folder-indexed. The fetch protocol is proven. The full organic end-to-end user flow is the next test.
- Phase 10-P MMLU-Pro (referenced elsewhere in the codebase): curated question bank, not the official MMLU-Pro out-of-bank evaluation. Do not compare directly to published MMLU-Pro leaderboard numbers.

**What these results are not:**
- An out-of-bank generalization benchmark
- A real-time web search accuracy test
- A comparison run on the same harness as flagships (Tier 3 is that comparison; it is pending)

**What is still being measured:**
- Tier 3: Gemma 4 12B + substrate vs flagships on the same harness (pending v0.1.27-full install)
- Organic mesh test: N=3 with each user independently indexing their own folder
- Audio Eblet performance (not yet implemented)
- Out-of-bank generalization on unseen question types

All results are published regardless of outcome. The prediction is locked to a commit hash. The replication kit is public. Check our numbers.

